Nergal.png 738w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Skills_Nergal-300x164.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 738px) 100vw, 738px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>*<em>Death &amp; Decay <\/em>is a spell that casts at the location on the battlefield in which the allied Panther unit was killed. The effect is similar to that of the Poison Cloud spell, but with +400% damage, +50% increase to the area of effect (radius), and +50% increase in duration<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>**<\/em>Each<em> Warrior Spirit <\/em>is an incarnation of Nergal himself, but with 50% Health and Damage of Nergal\u2019s base stats at Level 60. At each reduction of Nergal\u2019s total health by 30% (i.e. when 70%, 40% and 10% health remain), a <em>Warrior Spirit <\/em>will be summoned into battle on a random enemy troop location. These spirits act as a Poison Element Titan that can not only be controlled in battle, but also buffed by existing Relic and Skill effects that boost Poison Titan stats.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https:\/\/lh4.googleusercontent.com\/NBJOlL1ISNNvpbuZcMxulP1jwOqe-raxBm-RB3BR-6pRQsfZlkmb9xk9LKeqnyGO09u0O55F1cki5-QbT8nJ2ZGrGsOGfWi_B_W1txdsLSjJ7NizZBi5cV8aYMOiyrLvyy0FWEdo\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Nergal arrives with <strong>two new signature Relics<\/strong> alongside other powerful ones:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"687\" height=\"376\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Relics_Nergal.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-593\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Relics_Nergal.png 687w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/Relics_Nergal-300x164.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 687px) 100vw, 687px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Milestone Rewards<\/strong> are a